# Auto commit + push + deploy

After completing implementation changes in this repo (features, fixes, UI updates), **automatically** run commit, push, and production deploy without waiting for the user to ask.

## When to run

- Do this when meaningful code changes are done and build passes.
- Skip only if: user explicitly says not to deploy, changes are local/experimental only, or there is nothing to commit.

## Git

- Follow git safety protocol: never force push, never commit secrets (.env).
- Commit message: concise, focus on why (1 sentence).
- Push to `main` on `origin`.

## Deploy

- Production: https://rt.k-mkt.com
- VPS: `root@119.59.102.235`, app at `/var/www/rt_mkttools`
- SSH key: `~/.ssh/rt_mkttools_github_actions` (Windows: `%USERPROFILE%\.ssh\rt_mkttools_github_actions`)
- Command:
  ```bash
  ssh -i ~/.ssh/rt_mkttools_github_actions root@119.59.102.235 "bash /var/www/rt_mkttools/deploy/scripts/deploy.sh"
  ```

## After deploy

- Briefly tell the user: commit hash, that push/deploy succeeded, and what to verify on production.
